node.text:
2/3: ”The starting point of the Soft Side Table was to create something that was both subtle and characterful. Now, these two are often perceived as opposite poles, so the intent was to bring them together through softened surfaces and an understated yet sophisticated functionality,” says Fager, looking across the workshop that acts as part of his studio, located in a barn in the southern Swedish countryside.
—
Explore the story, now via link in bio. #muuto #newperspectives #scandinaviandesign

node.title: The Soft Side Table by Jens Fager

node.text:
2/2: On their thoughts behind the exhibition design for Ukurant Perspectives 2021, design duo Frederik Gustav says: “We knew from the get-go that we wanted the design to be an experience that strayed far away from the often polished exhibition formats that are shown at 3daysofdesign. The idea is really to get a sense of theatrical scenery."
—
Explore the full story, now via link in bio. #muuto #ukurant #newperspectives #scandinaviandesign

node.text:
1/2: In 2021, Muuto is supporting Ukurant, an exhibition platform and community for emerging designers with the ambition to facilitate and nurture future new perspectives on design. In the coming months, we will be visiting the studios of Ukurant and some of the creatives who partook in last year’s exhibition, exploring their spaces and hearing about their craft and perspectives on design.

Behind the exhibition design for this year's edition of Ukurant is Frederik Gustav, a Copenhagen-based design duo. Join us via link in bio as we visit them in their workspace to hear more about the origins of their collaboration, their ideas for the exhibition design for this year’s edition of Ukurant and to ask them what they believe makes something a new perspective.
—
Explore the story, now via link in bio. #muuto #ukurant #newperspectives #scandinaviandesign
